      "content": "The `ReactorBuilder` from `@powerhousedao/reactor` provides a fluent API for constructing reactors: `withDocumentModels()`, `withExecutorConfig({ maxConcurrency, jobTimeoutMs })`, `withWriteCacheConfig({ maxDocuments, ringBufferSize })`, `withMigrationStrategy('auto')`, `withKysely()` (defaults to in-memory PGlite), `withQueue()` (defaults to InMemoryQueue), `withEventBus()`, `withReadModel()`, `withSync()`, and more. Calling `build()` returns `IReactor`; calling `buildModule()` returns a `ReactorModule` exposing all internal components including operationStore, keyframeStore, writeCache, documentView, documentIndexer, readModelCoordinator, processorManager, and the underlying Kysely database.",
